author: CBC News
title: Doctors investigate rare COVID-19 symptoms in effort to move quickly from anecdotes to science
description: Dry cough, fever and difficulty breathing are the most common symptoms of COVID-19, but specialists are starting to learn more about less common potential symptoms such as loss of one's sense of smell, disorientation and even seizures.
